7:["$","main",null,{"className":"article-page","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Christian Dating Boundaries That Are Practical, Not Performative\",\"description\":\"A healthier way to talk about boundaries as shared protection, not shame or suspicion.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-10\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":\"https://bexhearts.com/blog/christian-dating-boundaries-that-are-practical\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Bexhearts\",\"url\":\"https://bexhearts.com\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Bexhearts\",\"url\":\"https://bexhearts.com\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"article-shell","children":[["$","$L12",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"back-link","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-arrow-left","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","1l729n",{"d":"m12 19-7-7 7-7"}],["$","path","x3x0zl",{"d":"M19 12H5"}],"$undefined"]}],"Blog"]}],["$","header",null,{"className":"article-hero","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"section-kicker","children":"Dating"}],["$","h1",null,{"children":"Christian Dating Boundaries That Are Practical, Not Performative"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A healthier way to talk about boundaries as shared protection, not shame or suspicion."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"article-meta","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-07-10","children":"2026-07-10"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[5," min read"]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"article-content","children":[["$","section","0",{"children":["$undefined",[["$","p","Boundaries work best when they are shared agreements, not rules one person uses to control the other.",{"children":"Boundaries work best when they are shared agreements, not rules one person uses to control the other."}],["$","p","For Christian dating couples, a good boundary answers a simple question: what helps us honor God, protect trust, and keep tenderness in the relationship?",{"children":"For Christian dating couples, a good boundary answers a simple question: what helps us honor God, protect trust, and keep tenderness in the relationship?"}]]]}],["$","section","Make boundaries specific",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Make boundaries specific"}],[["$","p","A vague boundary like “we should be careful” is hard to practice. A specific boundary like “we do not stay alone together past midnight” is easier to understand and easier to revisit.",{"children":"A vague boundary like “we should be careful” is hard to practice. A specific boundary like “we do not stay alone together past midnight” is easier to understand and easier to revisit."}],["$","p","Specific does not mean harsh. It means both people know what love is asking for in real life.",{"children":"Specific does not mean harsh. It means both people know what love is asking for in real life."}]]]}],["$","section","Review them without shame",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Review them without shame"}],[["$","p","The point is not to build a scoreboard. The point is to stay honest. Revisit your boundaries when schedules, stress, travel, or relationship stage changes.",{"children":"The point is not to build a scoreboard. The point is to stay honest. Revisit your boundaries when schedules, stress, travel, or relationship stage changes."}],["$","p","Bexhearts treats boundaries as part of a wider rhythm: prayer, check-ins, reflection, and intentional choices together.",{"children":"Bexhearts treats boundaries as part of a wider rhythm: prayer, check-ins, reflection, and intentional choices together."}]]]}]]}],"$L13","$L14"]}]]}]
